<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-09T12:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-09T12:29:00-05:00" n="357" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/362</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vologda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-09T20:00:00+02:31"><hi rend="italic">April 9,
                                            1918, 8 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 13, 5.43
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>84. Your 51, April 6, 6 p.m. I gave reasons for requesting railroad
                                men in my 73, April 5, 5 p.m., but as situation changed, better
                                defer sending until relations with Soviet government better
                                defined.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_FDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>